label.value: cell body rind of larval tritocerebrum

value.value: Region of the larval cell body rind that overlies the neuropil of the larval tritocerebrum.
Any neurosecretory neuron of the adult.
Any neurosecretory neuron of the larva.

label.value: adult Hugin neuron of the corpus allatum

value.value: Adult neuron that expresses Hugin and projects to the ring gland, where it has peptide release sites in the corpus allatum (Mizuno et al., 2021). It has synaptic contact with Dh44 neurons in the subesophageal zone (Mizuno et al., 2021). There are two of these cells per hemisphere (Mizuno et al., 2021), with their cell bodies in the subesophageal zone (Reinhard et al., 2023).

label.value: adult octopaminergic wing muscle motor neuron

value.value: Neuron that innervates a direct or indirect muscle of the wing via type II boutons (Stocker et al., 2018). It is octopaminergic (Stocker et al., 2018).
Adult neuron that innervates a muscle via type II boutons (Stocker et al., 2018). It is octopaminergic (Stocker et al., 2018).

label.value: adult octopaminergic neuron of abdominal ganglion

value.value: Any octopaminergic neuron (FBbt:00007364) that has its soma located in some cell body rind of adult abdominal neuromere (FBbt:00111086).

label.value: adult octopaminergic doublesex neuron of abdominal ganglion

value.value: Adult octopaminergic neuron of the abdominal neuromere that also expresses doublesex and is sexually dimorphic (Rezaval et al., 2014). There are more of these cells in the female (around 9) than the male (around three) (Rezaval et al., 2014).

definition.value: Thought to be octopaminergic based on Tdc2-GAL4 expression (Rezaval et al., 2014). These appear to be the only CNS octopamine/dsx neurons (Rezaval et al., 2014).

label.value: adult octopaminergic doublesex neuron of abdominal ganglion (male)

value.value: Adult male octopaminergic neuron of the abdominal neuromere that also expresses doublesex (Rezaval et al., 2014). There are approximately three of these cells in each male organism (Rezaval et al., 2014). They project to the male reproductive system, collectively innervating the ejaculatory duct, testes, and accessory glands (Rezaval et al., 2014).

definition.value: Thought to be octopaminergic based on Tdc2-GAL4 expression (Rezaval et al., 2014).

label.value: adult octopaminergic doublesex neuron of abdominal ganglion (female)

value.value: Adult female octopaminergic neuron of the abdominal neuromere that also expresses doublesex (Rezaval et al., 2014). There are approximately nine of these cells in each female organism (Rezaval et al., 2014). They project to the female reproductive system, collectively innervating the lateral oviducts, common oviduct, uterus, spermathecae, seminal receptacle and parovaria (Rezaval et al., 2014). These neurons are activated following mating and collectively mediate several post-mating responses (Rezaval et al., 2014; Yoshinari et al., 2020).

definition.value: Thought to be octopaminergic based on Tdc2-GAL4 expression (Rezaval et al., 2014).

value.value: Structure of the female reproductive system that is capable of storing sperm (Avila et al., 2012).

label.value: type II motor neuron of sperm storage organ

value.value: Motor neuron that innervates a sperm storage organ (spermatheca or seminal receptacle) with octopaminergic type II terminals (Avila et al., 2012). The seminal receptacle is innervated in the region proximal to the uterus and the spermathecal duct is innervated mainly in the distal third (Avila et al., 2012).

definition.value: Octopaminergic type II boutons identified based on bouton morphology and Tdc2-GAL4 expression (Avila et al., 2012). Not clear from Avila et al. (2012) whether each cell innervates both organs or whether there are subpopulations.

value.value: Neuron that innervates the peritoneal sheath or oviduct with octopaminergic type II terminals (Middleton et al., 2006). It reaches the reproductive system via the abdominal nerve to the ovary (Middleton et al., 2006). Octopamine stimulates the rupture of the posterior follicle cells prior to ovulation (Deady et al., 2017). These neurons also modulate contractions of these regions and movement of eggs out of the ovary (Middleton et al., 2006).

definition.value: Octopaminergic type II boutons identified based on bouton morphology and Tdc2-GAL4 expression (Middleton et al., 2006). Not clear from Middleton et al. (2006) whether each cell innervates both regions or whether there are subpopulations.

value.value: Epithelial layer of the uterus found interior to the muscle layer (Middleton et al., 2006). It is similar to the epithelium of the oviduct and may have a secretory function (Middleton et al., 2006).
Epithelial cell of the uterus. It has convoluted intracellular membranous structures, suggestive of a role in secretion (Middleton et al., 2006).

label.value: type I motor neuron of oviduct/uterus

value.value: Adult motor neuron that reaches the uterus or common oviduct via the abdominal nerve to the uterus and innervates the muscle layer with glutamatergic type I terminals (Middleton et al., 2006).

definition.value: Type I boutons identified based on bouton morphology, and Shaker and glutamate receptor expression (Middleton et al., 2006). Not clear from Middleton et al. (2006) whether each cell innervates both regions or whether there are subpopulations.

label.value: type II motor neuron of oviduct/uterus

value.value: Adult motor neuron that reaches the uterus or common oviduct via the abdominal nerve to the uterus and innervates the muscle or epithelial layer with octopaminergic type II terminals (Middleton et al., 2006).

definition.value: Octopaminergic type II boutons identified based on bouton morphology and Tdc2-GAL4 expression (Middleton et al., 2006). Not clear from Middleton et al. (2006) whether each cell innervates multiple regions or whether there are subpopulations.

label.value: adult octopaminergic leg muscle motor neuron

value.value: Octopaminergic neuron that innervates a leg muscle via type II boutons (Pauls et al., 2018). It fasciculates with the leg nerve (Pauls et al., 2018).

definition.value: Octopamine assessed based on expression of Tdc2-GAL4 (Pauls et al., 2018).

label.value: adult octopaminergic prothoracic leg muscle motor neuron

value.value: Any motor neuron (FBbt:00005123) that is synapsed via type II bouton to some muscle cell of adult prothoracic leg muscle (FBbt:00003343).

label.value: adult octopaminergic mesothoracic leg muscle motor neuron

value.value: Any motor neuron (FBbt:00005123) that is synapsed via type II bouton to some muscle cell of adult mesothoracic leg muscle (FBbt:00003402).

label.value: adult octopaminergic metathoracic leg muscle motor neuron

value.value: Any motor neuron (FBbt:00005123) that is synapsed via type II bouton to some muscle cell of adult metathoracic leg muscle (FBbt:00003430).

label.value: adult octopaminergic proboscis muscle motor neuron

value.value: Octopaminergic neuron that innervates a proboscis muscle via type II boutons (Pauls et al., 2018).

definition.value: Octopamine assessed based on expression of Tdc2-GAL4 (Pauls et al., 2018).

label.value: adult octopaminergic frontal pulsatile organ muscle motor neuron

value.value: Octopaminergic neuron that innervates the frontal pulsatile organ muscle via type II boutons (Pauls et al., 2018). It has its soma in the thorax (Pauls et al., 2018).

definition.value: Octopamine assessed based on expression of Tdc2-GAL4 (Pauls et al., 2018).

label.value: adult octopaminergic neuron of the corpus allatum

value.value: Adult octopaminergic neuron that fasciculates with the nervus corporis cardiaci and arborizes close to the corpus allatum (Pauls et al., 2021).

label.value: adult octopaminergic abdominal somatic muscle motor neuron

value.value: Adult octopaminergic neuron that innervates a somatic abdominal muscle via type II boutons (Pauls et al., 2018). These neurons collectively innervate at least the dorsal, ventral and lateral muscles of abdominal segments 2-6 (Pauls et al., 2018).

definition.value: Octopamine assessed based on expression of Tdc2-GAL4 (Pauls et al., 2018).

label.value: adult octopaminergic heart muscle motor neuron

value.value: Adult octopaminergic neuron that innervates a heart muscle cell via type II boutons (Pauls et al., 2018). These neurons collectively innervate at least the ventral longitudinal and alary muscles (Pauls et al., 2018).

definition.value: Octopamine assessed based on expression of Tdc2-GAL4 (Pauls et al., 2018).

value.value: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that has its soma located in some gnathal ganglion (FBbt:00004013).
Adult neuron that relays proprioceptive (body position) information from one or more sensory neuropil regions to one or more higher brain centers.
Procuticle of the pupa, it is composed of three distinct layers: exocuticle, endocuticle and assembly zone (Fristrom and Fristrom, 1993).
Procuticle of the adult. It does not have distinct exo- and endocuticle layers (Fristrom and Fristrom, 1993).
Procuticle of the larva. Its lamellae have a wavy morphology, which becomes more distinct throughout development, and are thicker in the basal region than the apical region (Tajiri et al., 2017).

Embryonic neuron that develops from the MP2 neuroblast and projects posteriorly (Thomas et al., 1984). There is one of these cells per hemineuromere and it is involved in establishing the longitudinal connectives (Thomas et al., 1984; Hidalgo and Brand, 1997). Before the end of embryogenesis, dMP2 cells of anterior neuromeres die by apoptosis, and those of posterior neuromeres (A6-9) develop into insulinergic cells that persist into the larval stage (Miguel-Aliaga et al., 2008).
Larval sensory neuron that innervates the dorsal trichoid sensillum DMSOh. There is one of these on each side, found in abdominal segment 8.
Larval sensory neuron that innervates the basiconic sensillum PLSOp. There are three of these per PLSOp sensillum, which is found in abdominal segment 9.
Any dch3 neuron (FBbt:00002010) that has its soma located in some larval prothoracic segment (FBbt:00001743).
Any dch3 neuron (FBbt:00002010) that has its soma located in some larval mesothoracic segment (FBbt:00001744).
Any dch3 neuron (FBbt:00002010) that has its soma located in some larval metathoracic segment (FBbt:00001745).
Sense organ of larval segment 10 that is comprised of a trichoid (hair) and a basiconic (peg) sensillum (Jurgens et al., 1987).

label.value: larval trichoid sensillum of anal sense organ

value.value: Trichoid sensillum of the larval anal sense organ (Jurgens et al., 1987).
Larval sensory neuron that innervates the trichoid (hair) sensillum of the anal sense organ.

Any interneuron of the larva.

Ventral region of the genital disc that derives from abdominal segment 8 (Keisman et al., 2001). By third instar stage, it constitutes the majority of the disc in the female, but a much smaller proportion in the male (Keisman et al., 2001). In females, it produces the majority of adult female genital structures, in the male it produces a miniature eighth tergite (Keisman et al., 2001).

Anterior region of the genital disc that derives from abdominal segment 9 (Keisman et al., 2001). By third instar stage, it constitutes the majority of the disc in the male, but a much smaller proportion in the female (Keisman et al., 2001). In males, it produces the majority of adult male genital structures, in the female it produces the parovaria (Keisman et al., 2001).

Posterior dorsal region of the genital disc that derives from abdominal segment 10 (Keisman et al., 2001). It gives rise to the adult analia (Casares et al., 1997; Keisman et al., 2001) and hindgut (Chen and Baker, 1997).
Female genital primordium of the female genital disc. It expands greatly during larval development and generates most of the female genital structures (Keisman et al., 2001).
